title: Ponta do Pargo (Ponta da)
body: The most extreme point of the western coast of Madeira is constituted by a rugged promontory, which is named Ponta do Pargo. This coastal promontory and its closest surroundings form a considerable part of that parish, where the lighthouse mentioned above is located.

Ponta do Pargo: Constituted by a rugged promontory, which is named Ponta do Pargo
